[[File:Korriban_Valley_TOR.jpg|thumb|250px|The [[Sith Academy (Korriban)|Sith Academy]] of [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]].]]
'''Sith academies''' were areas established to [[Sith training|train]] [[Sith/Legends|Sith]]. The [[Trayus Academy]], [[Sith Arts Academy]], and the [[Sith Academy (Korriban)|Korriban academy]] were academies established by the [[Sith Empire/Legends|Sith Empire]] and the [[Brotherhood of the Sith]]. The [[One Sith]] used the [[Temple of the Sith]] as its primary academy.

==New Sith Wars==
During the [[New Sith Wars]], academies were divided into four levels of student potential&mdash;[[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force sensitive]] [[Sith Warrior|Sith warriors]] and [[Sith Marauder|marauders]] were sent to some, potential [[Sith assassin/Legends|Sith assassins]] and [[Sith spy|spies]] to other [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] that have allied with the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] against the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]], potential [[Sith acolyte/Legends|Sith Acolytes]] and adepts to others, with the [[Sith Academy (Korriban)|academy]] on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]] being reserved only for potential [[Sith Master/Legends|Sith Masters]] or [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lords]]. In the academy on Korriban, there were six students for each Master.

